# RUN: tianchenrv-rvv-capability-profile-divergence-test | FileCheck %s

# The N1 probe->capability authority derives the capability DIVERGENCE axes
# (supported_sew / supported_lmul) from the real RVV probe ISA evidence, so a
# real probed profile can reach the legality gate (not only synthetic test IR).
# Two real probed profiles diverge on the SEW=64 axis: full-V (rv64gcv) admits
# it, the embedded zve32x profile rejects it -- capability-driven, on real ISA
# semantics.

# The deepest N1 axis (ISA generation): rv64gcv (RVV1.0) and rv64gc_xtheadvector
# (RVV0.7 / C920) share every SEW/LMUL axis but diverge on the rvv_version fact;
# the legality gate's ratified ta/ma policy split rests on it.

# CHECK: N1 full-V (rv64gcv) probe derives supported_sew=8,16,32,64 (SEW=64 admitted)
# CHECK: N1 zve32x probe derives supported_sew=8,16,32 (SEW=64 gated out)
# CHECK: N1 two real probed profiles DIVERGE on SEW=64: full-V admits, zve32x rejects (capability-driven)
# CHECK: N1 two real probed marches DIVERGE on RVV generation: rv64gcv=1.0 vs rv64gc_xtheadvector=0.7 (capability-driven)
# CHECK: N1 probe->capability stamps DIVERGENT RVV generation: rv64gcv=1.0 vs rv64gc_xtheadvector=0.7, support axes IDENTICAL (generation-only divergence)
# CHECK: RVV N1 probe->capability divergence-axis derivation tests passed
